result.formatted_address: 27～33 Kimberley Rd, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong
result.name: Kai Kee Restaurant

reviews.text:
Service was fast considering that every table was taken.  There are no lunch portions and most dishes could probably feed two. 

I was torn between giving this restaurant 3 and a 4 however.   The taste was very good but the food was tough. 

I ordered the curry beef brisket and needed to use a knife with some effort to cut it.  My wife ordered seafood with noodles. You actually needed a knife to cut the fish too!
On the ground floor directly on the street, a quick service for breakfast with a lot of buns, including pineapple buns
nice bolou bun. enjoyed it. breakfast sets.. not so
A 24 hour local food restaurant. Not bad food but not fast either. Had the rice and vegetables. The sauce was amazing. not a lot of English spoken so you point and pray. well worth it.
Excellent fresh baked buns in the morning. Great place to grab a quick bite to takeaway at the front of the store.

result.name: 佳記餐廳

reviews.text: 侍應服務態度惡劣 食物質甚差甚至下入流 不知所謂 唔會有下次
新鮮出爐麵包，軟林林，中西餐點，咖啡，奶茶，地方舒適。
服務親切，波羅包外酥內軟，凍檸茶清爽，非常好吃
最好的是任何時間都營業，食物選擇都不少，味道及衛生都算中上的，服務態度是沒以前好，但好像開始有改善，希望他們一直改進，我就繼續晨早有不錯的早餐吃
